Introduction: The hospital is still in short supply of protective materials, especially some general (disease) room.

By Wu Mianqiang

"We only started wearing protective clothing when there was a confirmed case [ of pneumonia with COVID-19 infection ] in our department recently, " Liu Xue (not her real name) , a nurse in a department at the Union Medical College Hospital, told reporters by telephone on the afternoon of January 30, their hospital is already running low on protective equipment.

On the same day, doctors at the Union Medical College Hospital released a request for help via the Internet saying that all medical supplies in the hospital were about to be exhausted, and they urgently requested social support, list: Urgent Need 3,000 protective clothing, medical N95 masks 5,000, medical surgical masks 8,000, disposable isolation clothing 3,000, protective masks 1,000, "these numbers are only a reference, in fact, the more the better. "

Liu Xue, a nurse who has worked for eight years, left her several-month-old child at home after the outbreak and insisted on working in the hospital. In order to do a good job of isolation, Liu Xue dare not go home after work, can only be admitted to the hotel outside the hospital.

Liu Xue told reporters that the hospital is still in short supply of protective materials, "announcements of the hospital's needs are often made to the public. Generally, when donated materials arrive at the hospital, the hospital will inform the medical staff of each department to collect them. But more often than not, the first thing that comes in is the fever clinic and the isolation ward, because they are the real frontline."

"The general ward is more dangerous than the isolation ward, because 'the enemy' is in the open, our department is 'the enemy' in the dark, and we can only know if we find out. Patients in our department are prone to fever, so it's not easy to tell what kind of fever it is,"she told reporters, the medical staff in the general ward are also at risk of being infected with the new type of pneumonia, but due to the shortage of materials, the medical staff in the general ward can only be allocated to the rear.

"To tell the truth, before all did not wear protective clothing, only recently appeared a confirmed case, we just arranged to wear. " Liu Xue voice began deep. "there is still concern that some close colleagues have been quarantined from coming to work. Today, I had a cough and went to the hospital for a CT scan. Fortunately, the results of the scan showed that my lungs were 'ok' and should be OK. If there was a problem, it would have been quarantined."

In fact, to date, there have been cases of general medical staff has been diagnosed with new pneumonia.

Liu Xue also said, "Some of the suits are thin, translucent and useless at first glance. I think everyone is well-intentioned, but it looks unprofessional and the quality is uneven. Including those goggles, we were given some ski goggles, which we didn't even have the other day, and our chief physician was doing rounds in goggles, and the patients were making fun of it. The medical staff in the ward have goggles in all colours, white, yellow, red, all colours."

Why do substandard protective equipment end up in hospitals? A hospital insider told reporters that protective materials for the hospital, has been very scarce, and in the current state of scarcity, it is estimated that hospital staff too late to review. "It's better to have it now than not to have it, " Liu said.

In fact, the Concorde Hospital made a request for the donated protective material. "The donated materials must meet national clinical standards or import standards, otherwise medical staff will not be able to use them, " according to a notice issued by the hospital

Some of the materials must meet or exceed the following standards: Chinese Medical Respirator: Gb19083-2010; N95 respirator: NIOSH certification, non-oil particulate filter efficiency ≥95% ; European N95 respirator: European FFP2 standard; KN95 respirator: Chinese GB 2626 Mandatory Standard, filtration efficiency of non-oil particulate matter ≥95% ; surgical mask: YY 0469-2011(Medical Surgical Mask) ; protective clothing: GB19082-2009"technical requirements for medical disposable protective clothing" ; medical protective clothing of Grade 2 and above (general clothing with red and blue stripes) ; GOGGLES: Medical Safety Goggles above level 2-Medical Safety Googles / Protective Eyewear, "donated materials need to be approved by the hospital before they can be sent for clinical use. "

Liu said that the shortage of protective materials did not only happen in her ward and hospital, but also many students and colleagues from different hospitals in Wuhan shared similar problems with her. Her description is similar to the information circulating on the Internet about the shortage of various hospital protective materials.

On the evening of January 30, at a press conference on the prevention and control of COVID-19 infection in Hubei Province, Cao Guangjing, vice governor of Hubei Province, responded to the issue of distribution of medical supplies, said to go all out to organize the province's enterprises to resume work, resume production, related enterprises 24 hours non-stop production. He predicted that in the next two to three days, Hubei can reach the production level of about 20,000 sets of protective clothing.
